So to get around that what you can do is you can add to your questions and they're very similar to like

01:39.890 --> 01:47.090
screener questions that we saw an up work on uptick we saw that they asked a question up front and the

01:47.090 --> 01:48.830
person has to answer to even bid.

01:48.830 --> 01:51.500
But this is actually going a little bit farther than that.

01:51.500 --> 01:59.330
So a key question is when you add a question or you add some kind of key instruction inside of the project

01:59.330 --> 02:03.970
description that only someone who read the project description would actually be able to see.

02:03.980 --> 02:11.690
So to give you an example you might say in your project description you know in your bid please say

02:11.690 --> 02:12.940
this phrase.

02:13.070 --> 02:19.010
That's a common one I've seen what they're basically trying to do is very quickly identify who has read

02:19.010 --> 02:20.400
and who has not.

02:20.420 --> 02:27.260
Now we don't use that technique because freelancers and freelance firms they can see each other's bids.

