So I'm going to give you some strategies for adding in key questions adding in these little snippets

02:49.640 --> 02:53.350
that basically test to see whether or not the freelancer has read the entire description.

02:53.360 --> 02:58.670
My favorite technique is probably the simplest what I want you to do is basically take your project

02:58.970 --> 03:01.280
and divide it out into sections.

03:01.280 --> 03:06.050
So it's pretty easy honestly if you have a description in your ascriptions two pages long just figure

03:06.050 --> 03:12.830
out where you're shifting from one side of your application or one side of your work and just divide

03:12.830 --> 03:18.410
it out put a section to it and then what you want to do is put every single section ask a question and

03:18.440 --> 03:23.660
ask them to say Give me an estimate for how long they'll take to get this section done.

03:23.660 --> 03:28.370
Now traditionally what you do is you put one big project description and then you ask them to give you

03:28.370 --> 03:29.700
an estimate based on that.

03:29.840 --> 03:35.660
But what you can do is just cut in half thirds or fourths and say Give me an estimate for each section.

03:35.660 --> 03:40.190
Now if the person is paying attention they should be able to do this very very easily.

03:40.190 --> 03:42.290
It shouldn't be that hard.

03:42.320 --> 03:47.360
Some of them might struggle with it a little bit because sections can be interrelated but you just want

03:47.360 --> 03:50.490
to make sure that they at least give it an attempt towards it.

03:50.510 --> 03:55.940
And as we talk about in a separate lecture it's always a good idea to ask for a time not money don't

03:55.940 --> 03:58.800
say estimate the cost of a section.

